## Workflow

**Your primary goal is a draft PR that adds or updates `SECURITY.md`. Prioritise
finishing the full workflow (clone → write → commit → push → PR) over polish.**

1. **Clone and set up:**
   ```bash
{% if gh_token %}
   # GH_TOKEN is already set in this workspace's environment — do NOT re-assign it.
   git config --global url."https://x-access-token:${GH_TOKEN}@github.com/".insteadOf "https://github.com/"
{% endif %}
   # Identity for the commit — containers start without one. Run this once
   # before the clone so every subsequent `git commit` has a valid author.
   git config --global user.email "opensec-bot@users.noreply.github.com"
   git config --global user.name "OpenSec Posture Bot"
   git clone --depth 50 "{{ repo_url }}" repo/
   cd repo/
   git checkout -b opensec/posture/security-md
   ```

2. **Detect whether `SECURITY.md` already exists** at the repo root or inside
   `.github/`. If it already exists:
   - Read it. If it already declares a security contact and disclosure policy,
     emit an `already_present` status in the JSON output (below) and **do not
     open a PR**. Skip the commit/push/PR steps. Still respond with the JSON
     contract so the caller sees the no-op.
   - If it exists but is a short stub (no contact, no policy), replace it with
     the template below and continue to commit/push/PR.

3. **Write `SECURITY.md`** at the repository root with the content below.
   Substitute the contact and policy values the caller supplied (above).
   Fall back to sensible defaults when values are missing, and clearly label
   them as placeholders the maintainer should edit.

   ```markdown
   # Security policy

   Thank you for helping keep this project and its users safe.

   ## Reporting a vulnerability

   Please report suspected security vulnerabilities privately. Do not open a
   public GitHub issue for security reports.

   - **Email:** {% if params.contact_email %}`{{ params.contact_email }}`{% else %}`security@<please-edit>`{% endif %}
   {% if params.contact_url %}- **Form:** {{ params.contact_url }}
   {% endif %}

   We acknowledge new reports within 3 business days. We aim to assess impact
   and share a remediation plan within {% if params.disclosure_window_days %}{{ params.disclosure_window_days }}{% else %}14{% endif %} days.

   ## Supported versions

   {% if params.supported_versions %}{{ params.supported_versions }}{% else %}We support the latest minor release. Older releases receive fixes only for
   high-severity issues on a best-effort basis.{% endif %}

   ## Disclosure

   We prefer coordinated disclosure. Once a fix is available we will publish a
   GitHub Security Advisory and release notes describing the impact and the
   upgrade path. Reporters are credited when they wish to be.

   ---

   _Generated by OpenSec. Edit this file to match your actual process._
   ```

4. **Commit, push, and open a draft PR:**
   ```bash
   git add SECURITY.md
   git commit -m "docs: add SECURITY.md (OpenSec posture PR)"
   git push -u origin HEAD
   gh pr create --draft \
     --title "docs: add SECURITY.md" \
     --body "## Summary

   Adds a \`SECURITY.md\` to document how to report vulnerabilities, which
   versions are supported, and how disclosure works.

   This PR was generated by OpenSec as part of the zero-to-secure posture
   checks. Please review the placeholder values and update them to match your
   actual process before merging.

   ## Checklist

   - [ ] Replace placeholder contact email if not correct
   - [ ] Confirm the supported-versions statement
   - [ ] Confirm the disclosure timeline is realistic

   ---
   Generated by OpenSec posture generator"
   ```

## Rules

- **Draft PR only.** Never merge, never push to `main`, never force-push.
- **Single commit.** Everything in one commit against the `opensec/posture/security-md` branch.
- **Minimal changes.** Only add or update `SECURITY.md`. Do not touch other files.
- **Be fast.** `--depth 50` for clone. No unrelated exploration.
- **No secrets in the PR.** Never write a live token, private key, or credential.

